# VAGRANT

$ vagrant up
  starts vagrant machine (provisions if not provisioned yet)
  
  # forces provision
  --provison 

  # forces specific provision to run
  --provision-with shell 

$ vagrant destroy
  destroys machine, leaves system in a clean state, all resources gone

  # no (manual) confirmation necessary
  -f 

$ vagrant suspend
  suspends the machine (rather than shutting it down via `halt`, or completely `destroy` it), consider it `sleeping` (all RAM contents saved)

$ vagrant halt
  shuts down `up` machine, tries to do it `graceful` 

  # force shutdown (even if `graceful` fails)
  -f 

$ vagrant provision
  provisions already `up` machine, new provision is without another `up`

$ vagrant status [MACHINE]
  shows status of machine(s)








